import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import tensorflow_data_validation as tfdv

from capacity_delay.features.target import target_in_seconds

data = pd.read_parquet('~/Documents/data/sclml/orders_branch_delays_friday_2019_2020.parquet')
del data['CourierCapacityDelay']
data['target_in_seconds'] = target_in_seconds(data)
data = data.dropna()
data.CreatedAt = pd.to_datetime(data.CreatedAt)
data.index = data.CreatedAt

reference = data[ data.CreatedAt < pd.Timestamp(2020,1,1) ] # 2019 data 
production = data[ data.CreatedAt > pd.Timestamp(2019,12,31) ] # 2020 data
In [55]:
def viz_stats(_ref, _prod, lhs_name, rhs_name):    
    print(f'{lhs_name} vs {rhs_name}')
    
    ref_stats = tfdv.generate_statistics_from_dataframe(_ref)
    schema = tfdv.infer_schema(ref_stats)
    prod_stats = tfdv.generate_statistics_from_dataframe(_prod)    
    
    tfdv.visualize_statistics(ref_stats, prod_stats, lhs_name, rhs_name)
    
    for col in ['delay', 'on_shift', 'on_duty', 'busy', 'available', 'waiting_orders', 'target_in_seconds']:
        tfdv.get_feature(schema, col).drift_comparator.jensen_shannon_divergence.threshold = .0 # for examination
    
    anomalies = tfdv.validate_statistics(statistics=prod_stats, schema=schema, previous_statistics=ref_stats)
    tfdv.display_anomalies(anomalies)
